This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for feature learning and extraction using deep neural networks. The paper also uses the CIFAR-10 dataset for training and the SVHN and STL-10 datasets for classification, which are commonly used in computer vision research, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of stochastic connectivity between neurons, which is a technique commonly used in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper's focus on efficient neural connectivity formation and its use of deep neural networks suggest that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's mention of embedded applications suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
